column2: Sunny- 85 F- lake level is lowering (severe drought)
Sunny- 85 F- had almost 2 inches of rain
Sunny- 80 F- had another inch since last observation
Day before fishing opener- lots of boat traffic- osprey on the nest on the powerpole on Popko Circle- across from the islands near our site.  Kit Bogenschneider recording data.
It's been a cool spring.  Kit Bogenschneider recording data.
Generally windy- but this site is protected from whitecaps most days.  Kit Bogenschneider recording.
Almost dead calm.  Kit Bogenschneider recording data
Kit Bogenschneider recording data.  Pretty day- winds nearly calm.
4th day of extreme heat- recorded by Kit Bogenschneider
Cloudless sky- breezy- data recorded by Kit Bogenschneider
clear sky- calm wind- lots of algae
First loon sighting of season yesterday 4/2/12
Light east wind- clear overhead- but clouds increasing
Had 1.4 inches rain 4 days ago and o.2 yesterday
Area had 0.7 inches rain 2 days ago.  Light chop on the water- partly cloudy skies.
Partly cloudy- very light breeze - just ripples on the water.
Heavy rain- 2.5 inches- a week ago
Gorgeous day- winds nearly calm- heard a crane- saw loons
Osprey has nest overlooking site. Saw a pair of loons and 1 heron.

We actually took the temperature and collected the water sample on 04/23/16.  This area was not deep enough to take a temperature at 15 feet.  It was cloudy so the secchi disk reading was taken on 05/02/16 (Disk did not hit the bottom as I accidentally reported).
